      <ReportItem port="3389" svc_name="msrdp" protocol="tcp" severity="4" pluginID="125313" pluginName="Microsoft Windows Remote Desktop Services Remote Code Execution (BlueKeep)" pluginFamily="Windows">
        <description>The remote Windows host is affected by a remote code execution vulnerability in Remote Desktop Services (CVE-2019-0708), also known as BlueKeep. An unauthenticated attacker can connect to the target via RDP and send specially crafted requests to execute arbitrary code. Network Level Authentication (NLA) is disabled on this host, increasing exposure.</description>
