        <description>The version of Apache HTTP Server running on the remote host is 2.2.34. It is therefore affected by multiple critical vulnerabilities including buffer overflow (CVE-2017-7679), use-after-free (CVE-2017-9798 / Optionsbleed), and request smuggling (CVE-2015-3183). Apache 2.2.x branch is end-of-life and receives no further patches.</description>
